Waverun City, as the commercial center of Iria, attracts many merchants from all over the world to trade.
After the discovery of the Luxite, the Papal States unilaterally declared the Luxite sacred to them and owned by them.
The Mornrays Castle was transformed into the capital from a military fortress during its vassal period.
The State of Iria, as a dependency of Papal States, was cruelly ruled by the Papal States via the royal family during the state period.
Faris, the present king, overthrew the State of Iria and established the independent Kingdom of Iria.
King Faris has been recuperating from the assassination attempt from several years ago, leaving Prince Dantalion to govern in his stead.
Iria achieved rapid recovery after independence through the Luxite trade, which also stored up trouble for the future.
The Crossroads Keep is a military fortress occupying a key locale within the lands of Iria, controlling the two core trade routes as well as supplies for Mornrays Castle.
Lightgloam City was the capital of the State of Iria but is now in a state of decline.
At the end of the War of Independence, Iria signed the Treaty of Iria with other states including the Papal States to achieve independence.
Under the terms of the Treaty of Iria, Iria ceded most of its territory and Luxite lodes to the Papal States.
To deal with the infiltration of enemy states and purge the enemies inside, Prince Dantalion founded a secret unit called "The Hanged Men."
Serving under Prince Dantalion, the "Hanged Men" have access to unlimited resources as well as authority.
Darklight's followers believe that rebirth comes after destruction, thus making the former their sole mission.
Union of Knight States is an alliance of several knight States that are powerful enough to influence the world.
Although its dominance has declined after the Radiant War II, the Papal States remain a dominant power.
The Elaman, a nomadic people, once destroyed and completely conquered ancient Iria.
Long, long ago, ancient Iria basked in abundance and prosperity under the stewardship of the Witenagemot.
On the new continent across the sea, an emerging state, the "Federation of Menia," was founded by former members of the Order and adventurers.
While the Papal States crave to grasp all the Luxite in this world, other nations seek to obtain and research Luxite as well.

<style=blue>Seeker</style> counters <style=red>Breaker</style>. <style=red>Breaker</style> counters <style=green>Defender</style>. <style=green>Defender</style> counters <style=blue>Seeker</style>. <style=yellow>Watcher</style> counters <style=purple>Destroyer</style>, and <style=purple>Destroyer</style> cannnot counter any roles.
The <style=green>green arrow</style> above the enemy in battle indicates that your character counters and deals bonus DMG to the targeted enemy.
The <style=red>red arrow</style> above an enemy unit indicates that your character is countered by them. Attacks against this enemy will deal less damage.
You can press and hold to drag units into position as required in battle.
Certain skills fly in a straight line at enemy units and can be blocked by other enemies in the trajectory.
During the battle, a character has four states: "Unharmed", "Healthy", "Injured", and "Dying"; "Injured" or "Dying" characters deal less damage and take more damage.
Units may gain "Physical Shield" or "Magical Shield" through various means in battle, which can block the corresponding DMG type.
Sunder DMG harms its target directly, surpassing the target's DEF attribute.
Environmental DMG refers to DMG taken by a character from objects, traps, terrains, devices, collisions, and falls.
When launching a single-target attack from a tile that is at least two tiles higher than the target tile, gains a [Highland] attack bonus.
Attacking a unit from [Behind] will trigger a [Back Attack], providing a DMG bonus.
After entering the terrain with a height difference ≥2 (uphill) in battle, each step costs extra Movement, resulting in a reduction in the actual movement distance.
The turn-based battle system that the turn is determined by "speed" is adopted in battle. Normally, each character can only act once a round.
After casting [Instant] skills, the character can still act.
In a character's turn, "move" precedes "attack", which is irreversible.
Curved shots have a parabolic trajectory and can avoid some obstacles.
The key to victory is to conduct crushing blows towards enemy, while observing their action order and movement ranges.
A character can equip up to 1 [Basic Attack], 1 [Reaction Skill], and 3 [Skills]. A good combination is the foundation of victory.
All characters acquire NRG after an action, but some classes can also acquire NRG in alternative ways.

1. Casting Tactical Skills consumes TP. 

2. TP recovers after a character's action or the round ends.

3. TP recovers upon triggering the following effects:

[Counter]: Attacking a unit countered by the character

[Highland]: Attacking from a highland

[Back Attack]: Attacking with Backstab

[AOE]: Dealing Crowd DMG to at least 4 enemies

[Collision]: Dealing Collision DMG to 2 enemies simultaneously

[Objects]: Make interactive objects/traps/devices effective

[Healing the Dying]: Healing dying characters

[Crowd Healing]: Healing 3 allies simultaneously

1. This is a pixel-style isometric terrain turn-based strategy game. It is recommended for users aged 12 and above, and minors are advised to use this game under parental guidance. 

2. The game tells a fantasy story in a fictional world. It features a distinctive pixel art style with vivid colors. The gameplay emphasizes strategic combinations, requiring a certain level of strategic thinking and encouraging players to hone their logical thinking skills to achieve game objectives. 

3. The game includes a user real-name authentication system. Authenticated underage users will be subject to the following restrictions regarding in-game purchases: Users under 8 years old cannot make purchases; users aged between 8 and 16 have a limit of 50 RMB per recharge, with a monthly cumulative limit of 200 RMB; underage users aged 16 and above have a limit of 100 RMB per recharge, with a monthly cumulative limit of 400 RMB. Online gaming services for underage users are limited to 1 hour per day on Fridays, Saturdays, Sundays, and legal holidays from 20:00 to 21:00. 

4. The game has a vast setting and a complex plot, fostering players' literary understanding and reading habits. Additionally, players need to continuously strengthen and improve their character's abilities during the adventure, contributing to the development of an optimistic, positive, and upward value system.
